Analysing an API Response

## Objective

Understand the structure of data returned by the API.

## API Endpoint

GET /identity/api/v2/vehicle/vehicles

## Observation

The API returned vehicle information in JSON format.

The response included:

- Vehicle ID
- UUID
- VIN
- PIN
- Vehicle model
- Manufacturer
- Fuel type
- GPS coordinates
- Vehicle status

## Key Learning

Unlike traditional websites, modern web applications exchange structured JSON data between the client and the server.

The browser reads this JSON response and dynamically displays the information to the user.

## Security Observation

The response contains unique object identifiers such as the Vehicle ID and UUID.

These identifiers are important because insecure authorization checks around object identifiers can lead to Broken Object Level Authorization (BOLA) vulnerabilities.

